			<p><img src="images\TriangleChoke.jpg" alt="TriangleChoke" style="float:left"><h1>Triangle Choke</h1>
			Head and arm choke using legs</br>
			Cross grip is hard to get, so easier setup is left hand grabs ops right wrist, right hand grabs ops right wrist, left hand moves to ops bicep.</br>
			From guard, righ hand grabs ops right wrist, left hand grabs ops right bicep. Right hand palm down, thumb and middle finger grip on wrist between wrist bone and hand.</br>
			Left hand grabs bicep just above elbow, thumb on outside, fingers inside, loose grip so fingers grip, not palm, right hand brings ops right hand to your hip to close the thumb/finger circle.</br>
			Keep your elbows in, left leg on ops hip to assist with moving 45deg/90deg, while right goes to ops left shoulder and point toes to slip past.</br>
			Left leg needs to be infront of ops shoulder, so it can push the arm into artery.</p>
